  section.main
    .row
      .small-12.columns
        h1= title
        p The Savory Institute promotes large-scale restoration of the world’s grasslands through holistic management. We use properly managed livestock to heal the land and empower others to do the same. We also remove barriers on the path to large-scale success through activities such as conducting research, creating market incentives and raising public awareness.


  #healing-the-land(data-magellan-destination='healing-the-land')
  section.main
    .row
      .small-12.columns
        h2 Healing the Land
        p The Savory Institute has joined with impact investors, Armonia, LLC and Level 3 Capital Advisors, LLC to create Grasslands, LLC. Grasslands identifies attractive ranch real estate investments, raises investor capital to purchase the assets, and then engages in long-term management contracts on the acquired properties.
        p A think tank called Capital Institute founded by Level 3 Capital Advisors’ principal John Fullerton has created a study called “Field Guide to Investing In A Resilient Economy”, of which Grasslands, LLC was the first subject. Read the study on the Capital Institute Web site.
        p As the Grasslands, LLC project grows,we foresee developing a “ranch real estate fund,” enabling investors to simultaneously participate in a portfolio of properties. The Grasslands team looks for properties that have the potential to provide triple-bottom-line impacts, including:
        ul
          li Major ecological benefits such as enhancing ecosystem resilience, sequestering carbon and building biodiversity.
          li Solid financial results through competitive annual cash dividends and low-risk, long term capital storage in the form of productive grassland.
          li Long-term stability for rural communities by providing employment opportunities for both experienced and up-and-coming land managers.
          li To date, Grasslands LLC is managing properties in South Dakota, Montana, Hawaii, and New Zealand. Total acreage under management is near 200,000 acres. These beautiful ranches support large herds of livestock all managed for land health under Holistic Planned Grazing. Grasslands is actively pursuing additional ranch purchases and management contracts worldwide. Grasslands is also collaborating with third party monitoring entities to objectively measure ecological, social and economic changes.
        p If you are interested in investing or working with the Grasslands LLC team, please contact the team at contact@savoryinstitute.com


  #removing-barriers(data-magellan-destination='removing-barriers')
  section.main
    .row
      .small-12.columns
        h2 Removing Barriers
        h3 Monitoring, Curating and Conducting Research
        p The Savory Institute conducts, coordinates and supports comprehensive social, ecological, and financial monitoring.
        p The Savory Institute has compiled and curated a portfolio of peer reviewed papers, articles, white papers and case study that represents the scientific and ground-truthed evidence basis of our work. We work in collaboration with organizations, scientists, and academic institutions to collect and conduct research that will increase our understanding of how properly managed livestock in the grasslands of the world contribute to removing carbon from the atmosphere and addressing problems such as drought, poverty, hunger and social violence.
        p We are currently working in collaborations with:
        ul
          li The Nature Conservancy
          li University of Wyoming – Haub School of Natural Resources and the Environment.
          li Princeton University – Ecology and Evolutionary Biology
          li Texas A&M University – Texas AgriLife Research
          li Idaho State University’s – GIS Training and Research Center
          li University of Pennsylvania – Applied Positive Psychology
          li Oregon State University – Geosciences
          li Agriculture Center for Excellence
          li Applied Eco Services
          li Land EKG
          li South Western Research Institute
          li South African Ag Research Council
          li Soil Carbon Coalition
          li Barrett’s Value Centre

        h3 Informing Policy and Programs
        p Policies and development programs concerning grasslands and livestock management in many countries are often flawed – and they are a major reason why desertification is expanding so rapidly around the world. The Savory Institute informs policymakers and stakeholders of the need to shift current agriculture and land management policies and programs. Savory Institute is a member of several global roundtables and dialogues, such as:
        ul
          li United Nations Convention to Combat Desertification (UNCCD)
          li United Nations Global Compact (UNGC) - Core Advisory Group - Member.
          li Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) Global Agenda for Action – Restoring the Value of Grasslands and Multi-Stakeholder Action for Sustainable Livestock – Member.
          li Global Roundtable for Sustainable Beef – Member.
          li Solidaridad - Farmers Support Program Pre-screening Committee – Member.
          li USAID’s Office of Foreign Disaster Assistance (OFDA)
          li Natural Resources Defense Council – Sustainable Grazing Metrics and Standards
          li The Nature Conservancy – 10-year collaboration on enhancing the role of science and conservation in the practice of Holistic Management.

        h3 Identifying and Establishing Market Incentives
        p The Savory Institute works to identify and establish strategies to create market-based incentives to encourage people to use Holistic Management to create environmental, economic and social benefits.  For example: Patagonia Inc.: we have joined a collaboration of sheep producers in Argentina which represent one of our first Savory Hubs in the Patagonia region, working with Patagonia, Inc. and The Nature Conservancy on a land management project that will restore 10 million acres of the Patagonia grasslands and add value to the wool produced on these estancias, Argentina.
        ul
          li US Beef Stewardship Collaboration - Sustainable Food Lab, USA
          li Armonia Sustainable Beef Program, USA
          li Massmart – South Africa
          li Marfrig – Latinamerica.
          li Increasing Public Awareness
          li The Savory Institute engages many different audiences to change public perception that livestock itself causes the degradation and/or desertification of grasslands. It is actually the way humans manage livestock that is the culprit. This fundamental shift in thinking must happen to drive needed policy and market shifts.

        p Many different key environmental activists and thought leaders are supporting our efforts to increase public awareness such as TED, HRH Prince of Wales, Deepak Chopra, Ian Somerhalder, Hazel Henderson, Gretel Erlich, and Peter Byck among others.
        p Media venues have featured the work of the Savory Institute, and several film producers, writers and independent journalists are working closely with the Savory Institute team to spread this knowledge.
        p The Savory Institute team is also available to speak at conferences, meetings and other gatherings.




