        h2 Partnerships
        h3 Global Partnerships
        p Throughout history, billions of dollars have been spent on solutions to desertification, which include resting the land, planting grass and trees, and developing machines to work or irrigate the soil. These solutions rely on large amounts of capital and expensive technology and are often culturally inappropriate. None of them have been successful in creating large-scale change. In fact, desertification has continued to accelerate at an alarming rate.

        p If we are going to create large-scale change on the ground, we must transform the way we think and act. Savory Institute believes that the restoration of the grasslands of the world, the fight against global climate change, the enhancement of water, food and nutrition security, and ultimately the wellbeing of all humans and living forms on Earth will take the collaboration of many aligned individuals and organizations.

        p The solution to the imminent global problems that are threatening life on Earth requires that we all join forces to find answers, innovative solutions, and political will to rethink the models that drive businesses, the way resources are allocated and distributed, the way science engages and informs resource management, the way we make our daily decisions as consumers, among other transformations.

        h4 Partner Network
